{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17608793","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17608793"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:36:41+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:36:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16015"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16015","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16015"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.44,0.16,0.12,0.24,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8706"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115188"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8706","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8706"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16015"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97196"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1891"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7567"},{"type":"tags","id":"8130"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20826"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20829"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115188","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115188"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ECleft palate is a common congenital anomaly that can occur either in isolation or as part of a syndrome. Understanding the anatomical involvement is crucial for proper diagnosis and management.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes isolated cleft palate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Failure of palatal shelves to fuse during weeks 6-12 of development","Defect limited to the soft palate and uvula only","Unilateral cleft extending through alveolar ridge","Incomplete fusion of maxillary and medial nasal processes","Defect involving both hard palate and lip"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFailure of palatal shelves to fuse during weeks 6-12 of development\u003C/strong\u003E correctly describes isolated cleft palate. This developmental defect occurs when the palatal shelves fail to elevate and fuse in the midline during embryonic development, resulting in a communication between the oral and nasal cavities.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDefect involving both hard palate and lip\u003C/strong\u003E describes cleft lip and palate, which is a different entity involving both structures. \u003Cstrong\u003EIncomplete fusion of maxillary and medial nasal processes\u003C/strong\u003E describes the embryological basis of cleft lip, not isolated cleft palate. \u003Cstrong\u003EDefect limited to the soft palate and uvula only\u003C/strong\u003E is too restrictive as isolated cleft palate can involve both hard and soft palate. \u003Cstrong\u003EUnilateral cleft extending through alveolar ridge\u003C/strong\u003E describes complete cleft lip and palate, not isolated cleft palate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIsolated cleft palate occurs without involvement of the lip or alveolar ridge and can range from a small defect in the soft palate to complete clefting of both soft and hard palate.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Isolated cleft palate occurs when the palatal shelves fail to fuse during weeks 6-12 of embryonic development.","Isolated cleft palate occurs without involvement of the lip or alveolar ridge.","Cleft palate can be syndromic or an isolated defect."],"references":["Falke, Goldman; Cleft Palate, https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK563128/, 2023","Vyas T, Gupta P, Kumar S, Gupta R, Gupta T, Singh HP. Cleft of lip and palate: A review. J Family Med Prim Care. 2020 Jun 30;9(6):2621-2625. doi: 10.4103/jfmpc.jfmpc_472_20. PMID: 32984097; PMCID: PMC7491837","Pang J, Broyles J, Redett R. Cleft lip and palate. Eplasty. 2013;13:ic25. Epub 2013 Jan 30. PMID: 23409216; PMCID: PMC3567612","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97196"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16015"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97196","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97196"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-23T09:33:26+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-23T09:34:47+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8706"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115188"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suita